<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer15294136734366750962"><strong>Robert M. Edsel</strong> is the best-selling author of <em>Saving Italy</em>, <em>The Monuments Men</em> and <em>Rescuing da Vinci</em> and co-producer of the award-winning documentary film <em>The Rape of Europa</em>. Edsel is also the founder and president of the Monuments Men Foundation, a recipient of the National Humanities Medal, and a trustee at the National WWII Museum. After living in Florence for five years, he now resides in Dalla</span>
  <span id="freeText15294136734366750962" style="display:none"><strong>Robert M. Edsel</strong> is the best-selling author of <em>Saving Italy</em>, <em>The Monuments Men</em> and <em>Rescuing da Vinci</em> and co-producer of the award-winning documentary film <em>The Rape of Europa</em>. Edsel is also the founder and president of the Monuments Men Foundation, a recipient of the National Humanities Medal, and a trustee at the National WWII Museum. After living in Florence for five years, he now resides in Dallas, Texas.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15294136734366750962" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

